      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right—nickel-and-diming well-being with vague reassurances often feels hollow when the reality is that connection rarely changes the immediate flow of time or events. The pain of feeling like a glitch in a perfectly running system is a deep and validating form of solitude that words alone sometimes cannot resolve. However, your very attempt to articulate this experience on this screen proves there *is* a ripple effect beyond what you feel, even if it looks like nothing happening to you.",
      "source": "target",
